import sys
import os

import time

email = "testuser@saasglue.com"
password = "mypassword"

platform = "linux"
arch = None

outFile = '{}/sg-agent-launcher'.format(workingdir)
def RestAPILogin():
    global token
    global email
    global password
    url = 'http://kiki-go-server.herokuapp.com/login/apiLogin'
    
    headers = {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json'
    }
    data = {
        'email': email,
        'password': password
    }
    res = requests.post(url=url, headers=headers, data=json.dumps(data))
    if (res.status_code != 200):
        raise Exception(
            'Call to {} returned {} - {}'.format(url, res.status_code, res.text))
    token = res.cookies.get_dict()['Auth']
def GetDownloadUrl():
    global token
    global teamId
    global platform
    global arch
    while token == '':
        RestAPILogin()
        if token == '':
            print('API login failed')
            time.sleep(5)
            print('Retrying api login')
    url = 'https://kiki-go-server.herokuapp.com/api/v0/agentDownload/agentstub/{}'.format(platform)
    if arch:
        url += ('/' + arch)
    headers = {
	'Cookie': 'Auth={};'.format(token),
        '_teamId': teamId
    }
    while True:
        res = requests.get(url=url, headers=headers)
        if (res.status_code == 200):
            break
        else:
            if (res.status_code == 303):
                time.sleep(10)
            else:
                raise Exception(
                    'Call to {} returned {} - {}'.format(url, res.status_code, res.text))
    return res.json()['data']
def DownloadAgent():
    global outFile
    s3url = GetDownloadUrl()
    res = requests.get(s3url, allow_redirects=True)
    open('sg-agent-launcher.gz', 'wb').write(res.content)
    with gzip.open('sg-agent-launcher.gz', 'rb') as f_in:
        with open(outFile, 'wb') as f_out:
            shutil.copyfileobj(f_in, f_out)
    os.chmod(outFile, 0o777)
    os.remove('sg-agent-launcher.gz')
DownloadAgent()
configFile = '{}/kiki.cfg'.format(workingdir)
with open(configFile, 'w') as f:
    json.dump(config, f, indent=4)
os.system('su - ec2-user -c {}'.format(outFile))
